# PDPP Railway Core deploy target environment block
#
# Selected pushbutton shape: one public application service named `core` plus a
# Railway Postgres plugin. The `railway-core` image runs the console on
# Railway's injected $PORT and runs the reference AS/RS privately on loopback in
# the same container.
#
# Use core.env.example as the service-specific template. The older
# console.env.example/reference.env.example split-service files remain available
# for manual operator experiments, but they are not the published button path.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# core service (public) — one internet-reachable origin.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
PDPP_REFERENCE_ORIGIN=https://${{core.RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN}}
# Optional: comma-separated extra hostnames permitted as forwarded hosts.
PDPP_TRUSTED_HOSTS=

# Owner gate — REQUIRED. Set a non-empty, high-entropy value as a Railway secret.
# The owner-session signing key derives from this value, so a stable password
# keeps owner sessions valid across restarts.
PDPP_OWNER_PASSWORD=

# Instance-level wrapping key for owner-captured static-secret connector
# credentials. The published template should generate this automatically.
PDPP_CREDENTIAL_ENCRYPTION_KEY=${{ secret(64) }}

# Durable storage — selected button path uses Railway Postgres.
PDPP_DATABASE_URL=${{Postgres.DATABASE_URL}}

# Do not set these as Railway variables on the selected core service. The image
# and supervisor own the topology constants so Railway does not prompt for them:
# PORT, AS_PORT, RS_PORT, PDPP_AS_URL, PDPP_RS_URL.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Manual fallback only: SQLite on a mounted persistent volume.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PDPP_STORAGE_BACKEND=sqlite
# PDPP_DB_PATH=/data/pdpp.sqlite
